      "rationale": "Fluid density and viscosity are sourced from calibrated rheometry (±1.5%). Blood damage model constants (Giersiepen power-law coefficients) are taken from peer-reviewed literature. Geometric inputs derive from CMM measurements of the physical pump (±0.02 mm). Input uncertainty is within acceptable bounds for MRL 2. The experimental baseline dataset (dataVintage 2025-10-17) was collected under the prior model build; the November 2025 revision adjusted impeller tip-clearance mesh topology only. The modelling team assessed this change as non-material to the constitutive law inputs and boundary conditions represented in the dataset, and no formal re-validation was performed against updated simulation outputs."
