    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/decision/cou1-accepted-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/morrison/actor/credibility-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed the required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are not assessed, which is acceptable at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 3. The primary experimental dataset (fda-pump-experimental-baseline) carries a dataVintage of 2025-10-17, which predates the model revision of 2025-11-10 by approximately three weeks. The modelling team's internal memorandum (ref. CVL-2025-114) concludes the revision was limited to impeller tip-clearance mesh topology and does not affect the boundary condition inputs or constitutive model parameters captured in the experimental dataset. On this basis the dataset is considered fit for purpose without re-validation. The RH < 1 acceptance criterion is satisfied at all five operating points. The assessment team accepts the COU claim.",
